
GGC - GNU Gluco Control
=======================

This are short instruction on how to star application. As prerequisite you need to have java 1.5 
or higher installed.


A) How to start software
=========================

1.) Windows

After install program should run by itself (by clicking on icon), if you are not sure where problems 
lie, run cmd.exe (command line shell) and run following command: run_win.cmd. Error should be written 
somewhere on screen. 
In most cases problem is with java path ('java' is not recognized as an internal or external command,
operable program or batch file). In this case follow instructions under C): 1.


2.) Linux
On linux platform you need to issue following command 'sh run_linux.sh'. If application doesn't start
see on screen where the problem is. 
Same as in Windows section (A.1) in most cases problem is with java path (see section C.1. on how to 
resolve this)

3.) Mac
On Mac platform you need to issue following command 'bash run_mac.sh'. If application doesn't start
see on screen where the problem is. 
Same as in Windows section (A.1) in most cases problem is with java path (see section C.1. on how to 
resolve this)




B) Support for meters
======================

In some future version, we will add support for meters. For this purpose, we have special library, which 
needs to be installed. In most cases installation is very simple, open zip file in \lib (rxtx something)
and find your OS and architecture type and copy file to bin folder. In some casses you need to copy this 
files to Java Runtime folder in subfolder \bin.

Supported OSes at this time are: Windows (x32, works with x64), Solaris (32/64), Mac OS X, Linux (x32, 
ia64, x64).

If you have USB device, you should configure USB so, that it will show virtual COM port.




C) Troubleshooting
===================

1.) Java Path is not correct
----------------------------

a) Change path in StartupConfig

Open StartupConfig.properties with your favorite editor. Change JAVA_EXE parameter to point to your java 
executable (if you have Windows you should enclose path in " ", so that whole path is used. Also if you 
use \, you should use doubles (\\), like "c:\\Program Files\\Java\\jre_1.5.0_06\\bin\\java.exe". When 
this file is read single \ are removed.


b) Change path in startup file (see section D)

Open startup file and change path to java, similar to change in C.1.a, but here you must use single \ instead
of double (like: "c:\Program Files\Java\jre_1.5.0_06\bin\java.exe")


